Two unidentified brothers of a widow, Mrs. Ogechukwu Thankgod, have drowned at a canal in Akiama community, Bonny Local Government Area, Rivers State. The Chairperson of Bonny, Dame Anengi Barasua, was said to have led a delegation to commiserate with the family of the deceased. The Deputy Press Secretary to the chairperson, Boma Waribor, confirmed the sad development in a statement at the weekend.   Five killed, scores injured in renewed Bayelsa cult war     Truck driver kills two passengers in Anambra accident     UPDATED: Court rejects suit challenging Atiku’s…   He said Barasua, who was represented by her Chief of Staff, Austin Onu Pepple, grieved over the incident that occurred on Saturday. - Advertisement - While promising to help the widow, Barasua called on community leaders Bonny to build fortifications around dangerous areas within their domains. “The loss of two children by a widow in one day and in such horrendous manner is a painful experience and we pray that the bereaved mother, Mrs Ogechukwu ThankGod will find peace,” she said. SPONSORED